  23 Apr 2009; Mounir Lamouri <volkmar@gentoo.org> pms-2.ebuild,
  pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Add ~ppc keyword

  18 Apr 2009; Thomas Anderson <gentoofan23@gentoo.org> pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Fix filenames to sed for set-options, dependent on USE=eapi3-draft

  17 Apr 2009; Thomas Anderson <gentoofan23@gentoo.org> pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Fix Build Dependencies, USE=html needs >=dev-tex/tex4ht-20090115_p0029

  16 Apr 2009; Christian Faulhammer <fauli@gentoo.org> pms-99999999.ebuild:
  add dev-tex/leaflet as the EAPI 3 branch now needs that

  15 Apr 2009; Christian Faulhammer <fauli@gentoo.org> pms-99999999.ebuild:
  add dependency on dev-texlive/texlive-bibtexextra for EAPI 3 branch

  13 Apr 2009; Christian Faulhammer <fauli@gentoo.org> pms-2.ebuild,
  pms-99999999.ebuild:
  add ~x86 KEYWORD

*pms-2 (13 Apr 2009)

  13 Apr 2009; Christian Faulhammer <fauli@gentoo.org> +pms-2.ebuild:
  add an ebuild which installs the approved EAPI 2 version of the PMS

  12 Apr 2009; Christian Faulhammer <fauli@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  add ulm and myself as maintainers

  26 Mar 2009; Thomas Anderson <gentoofan23@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Add EAPI 3 draft support, thanks to David Leverton for the patch

  29 Sep 2008; Ferris McCormick <fmccor@gentoo.org> pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Add ~sparc keyword.  This builds fine, as it is nothing but a git pull and a
  latex build.  This is needed to facilitate recommendation from Council that
  one should 'emerge app-doc/pms' for some EAPI=2 documentation.

  29 Sep 2008; Thomas Anderson <gentoofan23@gentoo.org> pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Add ~amd64 keyword

  24 Aug 2008; Thomas Anderson <gentoofan23@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Picking up maintainership

  16 Aug 2008; Torsten Veller <tove@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Remove ingmar from metadata.xml (#202413)
  Remove zlin from metadata.xml (#202412)

  24 Jul 2008; Doug Goldstein <cardoe@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  add GLEP 56 USE flag desc from use.local.desc

  15 Jun 2008; Ingmar Vanhassel <ingmar@gentoo.org> pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Add a html USE flag, to generate pms as HTML as well. Patch by David
  Leverton.

*pms-99999999 (13 Jun 2008)

  13 Jun 2008; Ingmar Vanhassel <ingmar@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
  +pms-99999999.ebuild:
  Import app-doc/pms, an ebuild for the latest pms.pdf draft. ebuild by
  David Leverton.

